Rationale: Figure 1: Overexpression of the phospho-blocking T1067A CYFIP2 mutant affects stubby spine density and neurite outgrowth in cultured hippocampal neurons.. Experimental description: biological system used for experiment; "Cultured hippocampal neurons were prepared from rat brains of 18-day-old embryos"

human protein was used for overexpression;
"The full-length human CYFIP2 cDNA (pOTB7 CYFIP2) was purchased from Open Biosystems and subcloned into the pEGFP-N1 plasmid (Clontech, Mountain View, California, USA). Mutagenesis reactions were performed using the QuikChange II XL Site-Directed Mutagenesis Kit (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, California, USA) according to the manufacturer's instructions to generate pEGFP-N1 full-length S582A, S582D, T1067A, T1067E, and S968F CYFIP2 construct"
